  "text": "Stx1 and Stx2 are encoded in the genome of lambdoid prophages which are designated Stx-converting bacteriophages [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Stimuli such as UV light or mitomycin C are known to induce these prophages. As a result of the induction process, bacterial host cells lyse and release mature IP: 54.70.40.11",
